		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Halfling Druid Guide, lvls 1-6</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:explosionman500@aol.com">Meis Triumph</a> | 
		            1/26/2001 4:26:21 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">LvL 1-6 Druid Guide<BR>
stats: add +5 to agi and +25 to wis<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
guide: you start out in Rivervale. First, take your guild note to your guild to get some exp and a tunic, whch you should then equip. Put your 5 practice points into 1Hand Slash (yes, i know you start with a blunt weapon but trust me!) Then go outside into Misty.<BR>
					You start the game with Minor Healing and Skin like Wood. Before your first battle, equip your cheap piece of shit club (after some battles and a lvl gained, buy a 1H slasher) , memorize your spells,  and cast Skin like Wood on your self. After casting, you will take a little damage when the spells affect begins. You can counter this with Minor Healing, or just wait about 10 seconds. When you are ready to fight, choose a monster who cons even to you (probably the large rats) and run up to it and start to fight. -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR>
Spells:<BR>
I would reccomend first buying Burst of Flame, and using my tactic down below. The second spell you should buy is Snare. You can then Kite* the monsters. First cast Snare, then run back a little, then cast a few Burst of Flames. Run back some more and repeat this process until Snare runs out, then melee it to death. Continue this untilyou've got enough cash to upgrade your Kitting abilities. The next spell is Flame Lick. This is a small DoT (around 10 total) and decreases AC (around 10 aswell.) Now you can do the same thing, but after Snare, cast Flame Lick, then continue. You will also need a Fire Beetle Eye to cast Flame Lick, but it won't be consumed. The best way to do this is to kill a fire beetle, then put the eye in your second hand. Now you will see a little better in the dark (Misty is always dark) and it wont take up an inventory slot in order to cast Flame Lick. The last spells to buy are Endure Fire, Dance of the Fireflies, and Sense Animals. Endure Fire is a good buff spell against a caster who casts fire spells. Dance of the Fireflies and Sense Animal are pretty much only used to raise your skill in Conjuration and Evocation, although Dance does produce a no drop light source (but you do have that eye, right?)<BR>
<BR>
LV1 (1-2 gold) spells you must buy<BR>
Flame Lick (and fire beetle eye) 10<BR>
Snare 15<BR>
Burst of Flame 7<BR>
Minor Healing 10<BR>
Skin Like Wood 10<BR>
Endure Fire 20<BR>
Dance of the Fireflies 10<BR>
Sense Animals 5<BR>
<BR>
Secret: I picked this up while fighting a fire beetle at lvl 1. I was about to die when i just decided to cast Minor Heal. Usually when you cast while Melee fighting, you will be interrupted. This time i wasn't. I found out if you begin to cast the spell right before it hits you (no, you won't get the spell's affect till after it hits you) it will either: A. hit you, or B. miss. After a or b happens, the spell will take effect. By hitting (or missing) you at the start of the spell, it won't interrupt you. I usually use this with Burst of Fire (or Burst of Flame if below lvl 5) to hit the monster with my sword (which was given to me by another generous druid) and hit it with a spell. Very cool.<BR>
NOTE: if you're still lvl 1 and got a DD spell (Burst of Flame) i wouldn't recommend using this tactic on a high yellow or red mob, because there is a 97.5% chance of you getting killed and leaving yet another body on Misty's floor.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
LvL 5<BR>
guide: Now you should probably have 1 or 2 more pieces of leather, a bag, and a 1H slasher. Go buy some lvl 5 spells and then head over to the harder side of Misty, past the gates. (I did this at 4 and 1/2) You can solo Shadow Wolves or group at a Goblin camp (soloing gives more loot/exp, but grouping is much more fun)<BR>
<BR>
Spells:<BR>
lvl 5. Now your almost out of newbie-hood. First spell to buy? Solo = Grasping Roots.<BR>
But Grouping = Invoke Lightning. Why? When i first grouped at 5, (i made my own group, as i am good at doing that) my members wanted to fight at one of the three goblin camps. Seeing as how there are usually 2 or 3 goblins, and we fought them all at once (Harmony can fix that, but we wanted the challenge) i chose this AE (area affect) spell. I just waited until 2 or 3 goblins spawned, then used my Caster Pull (the caster, me, pulled instead of the tank, by using a spell.)<BR>
This did about 22 damage to each monster, which was a really good way to start out. There is a small danger to using this spell though. After casting, the monsters go aggro on the caster, so a few tanks should be ready to get in there. The second spell i bought was Gate. This spell speaks for itself. It was also a good way to get to the entrance to RV to sell loot without going through the monster infested path. Third spell - Whirling Wind. It does about 24 damage and has a short stun, and costs 8 less mana than Invoke. The fourth spell i bought because of something that ALWAYS happened during downtime. While i recovered mana (at lvl 5 druids don't have med yet) i would solo (while still in the group) some snakes, just for a little more exp, but every time i would get poisoned. It wasn't too bad, all i had to do was cast Minor Heal for a while, but i'd rather have just gotten rid of it all together. So i bought Cure Poison. That helped. (NOTE: while fighting asps in the East Commons, i had to cast it about 3 or 4 times on the tank until he was healed) Then i bought Camoflauge and (finally) Harmony. When i desided to solo for about 3/4 of a lvl i picked up the root spell (Grasping Roots.) At lvl 6, none of my Halfling buds were on (different time zone) so i ran over to Freeport. This was very hard and took about an hour because it was night time and in Kithicor there are tons of undead. Believe it or not, when i went through Kithicor, there was no one else in the zone! Wierd. I died twice (zombie and an undead healer) before i got to FP (Camo was a life saver, literaly) and grouped with an enchanter there. We decided to try to kill asps without a tank (kinda hard at lvl 6) but with her de-buffs and my root/heals, we got to 7 in no time. We finally decided to get a tank, so we picked up a Dwarf at the entrance to NRo. That was a big mistake. He pulled like 4 asps at a time, then i latter found out he was lvl 10 and took all the exp! Plus i had died about 5 times (now i',m at 6 and 1/2 again!)<BR>
Then i got ported to nKarana and ran to Qeynos. I soloed large and giant bats using Root, Flame Lick, and Whirling Wind.<BR>
...Well, that's it for now, I'll post more later. <BR>
<BR>
LVL5 (under 1pp) Spells you must buy<BR>
Camouflage 15 mana<BR>
Whirling Wind 24 mana<BR>
Invoke Lightning 32 mana<BR>
Burst of Fire 15 mana<BR>
Gate 70 mana<BR>
Harmony 25 mana<BR>
Cure Poison 20 mana<BR>
Cure Disease 20 mana<BR>
Grasping Roots 35 mana<BR>
